d  Must be able to manage multiple priorities and projects simultaneously  Skilled in problem/incident management, SLAs  Service Level Agreements and full lifecycle system support  Excellent verbal/written communications skills. Strong presentation and negotiation/conflict resolution skills  Experience in Pharmaceutical, Biotech, or other validated environment highly desired Roche is an equal opportunity employer.','Job Type fulltime ,  contract','https://job-openings.monster.com/business-analyst-with-sap-fico-south-san-francisco-ca-us-infosmart-technologies-inc/225467679'),(10,'BA/QA Analyst','TOPSYSIT','','Business Analyst','Full Job Description Are you ready for a change? Want to join a dynamic and fast-growing company with amazing benefits then we welcome you to view our position. We are seeking an experienced Business Analyst/ Quality Analyst to work remotely! Interested in learning more? Keep reading. The primary responsibilities of the Business Analyst are to evaluate data, business processes, anticipate requirements, uncover areas for improvement, and develop and implement solutions related to data in various data sources. Identify and analyze data related business problems and define the scope of activities required to address the issues, including requirement definition, process review, impact assessment, training improvements and operational streamlining where appropriate. WHAT THE BUSINESS ANALYST DOES ON A DAY-TO-DAY BASIS: Lead ongoing reviews of business/data processes and developing optimization strategies Act as a project coordinator by working with key individuals to implement data sharing procedures and Data Governance standards Identify key areas for process documentation and/or improvement through data analysis and strategic thinking Work with management, business users, and technical staff to understand business processes, desires, and problems to be addressed Participate in Change Management meetings and document any changes to data related pr