 insights and commentary to help simplify and explain complex trends REQUIREMENTS (Minimum 2+ years experience in the following):  Experience creating visualizations within Tableau and cleaning / merging data with Tableau Prep and Python.  Experience with MySQL databases and joining large datasets  Advanced Excel skills (eg pivot tables, lookup formulas, etc) including the ability to manipulate and manage large datasets.  A Bachelor\'s degree with a solid GPA from a reputable four-year institution.  Intellectual curiosity and a desire to understand the forces that are driving the trends in the data.  Strong interpersonal skills; ability to listen closely to whats being said and whats not being said, and to pick up on non-verbal communication.  Attention to detail is critical to success in this role. A candidate should place a considerable importance on the quality of their work and ensure the small yet important details are not missed.  Organizational and time management skills and the ability to work productively and efficiently in a fast-paced environment with multiple projects and tight deadlines.  A self-starter with the ability to work independently and manage their own workflow. A candidate should work well with minimal supervision and take ownership on project completion.  Work as an effective, collaborative member within a small team environment. We all get our hands dirty and do whatever it takes to produce quality research. We provide competitive compensation based on experience, a performance bonus (up to 25% of base), health insurance, 401K, and Commuter Benefit options. Cover letter optional. Please be advised we are not able to offer employer sponsorship for this position. Job Type: Full-time Pay: $85,000.00 - $100,000.00 per year COVID-19 considerations: Working remotely until we can safely report back to our offices in Oakland, then we will be strictly on-site','Salary $85000  -  $100000   Per Year','https://job-openings.monster.com/market-research-d