e optimization and management. The solution fully supports multi-cloud environments such as Amazon Web Services (AWS), Azure, Google Cloud, IBM Cloud and private cloud deployments.  The Data and AI Expert Labs organization is looking for Entry Level Data Engineer / Data Analyst to join the Cloud Pak for Data organization to support deployments and/or support of the technology for clients.What youll do as an Entry Level Data Engineer / Data Scientist in the Expert Labs Cloud Pak for Data organization: Your Role and Responsibilities What youll do as an Entry Level Data Analyst / Data Engineer in the Expert Labs Cloud Pak for Data organization:     Deploy Cloud Pak for Data for IBM clients across various platforms     Help define Cloud Pak for Data architectures that operationalize the platform and map relevant client use cases to satisfy key stakeholders and drive business value     Assist our Cloud team for any support activities for our customer deployment     Assist client development teams with Cloud Pak for Data environment setups, testing scripts, deployments, and production operational metrics/debugging information     Leverage customer data assets to optimize profitability, grow customer relationships, improve experience and satisfy business need     Ensure consistent data quality, establish data standards and governance, integrate data between on premise and cloud both operationally and analytically     Optimize data retrieval and develop dashboards, reports and other visualizations for stakeholders     Communicate with internal and external clients to understand business needs and deploy successful analytical solutions     Work in an agile, collaborative environment, partnering with other scientists, engineers, and database administrators of all backgrounds and disciplines to bring analytical rigor and statistical methods to the challenges of predicting behaviors Who You Are: You have strong technical and analytical abilities, a knack for driving impact and 