INSERT INTO `bay_area_ma` VALUES (0,'Marketing Analyst','Randstad','San Jose, CA','Marketing Analyst','  We are looking for someone with Marketing project management experience to help manage cross-functional Marketing assets and internal projects. In this role, you will work with the GTM Marketing teams such as Web Development, Creative, Marketing Operations, Digital Marketing, Field Marketing, and more to drive progress on Marketing initiatives and projects. This role requires someone with experience working on website enhancements, branding campaigns, email marketing, and more. You will work with the team to manage prioritization and develop processes to make your team more efficient and effective. Communication and collaboration are your strong suits as you will be the owner of the process and must be solutions oriented. The role will report to our Director of Marketing Project Management, and would be a great fit for someone looking to strategically influence a fast paced marketing organization. Responsibilities  Manage an intake for team requests, prioritize projects within the team, and collaborate with marketing leads in assigning appropriate resources to projects \n Work collaboratively with Creative, Content, Web, Marketing Ops, Digital Marketing, and Events teams as cross- functional partners \n Develop and update project plans/workback schedules for multiple projects, and execute on milestones and deliverables with realistic deadlines \n Identify risks, create contingency plans, and provide creative solutions in a dynamic environment \n Anticipate, oversee and troubleshoot any potential problems within our creative and cross-functional teams, and manage implications in terms of priorities, tasks, resources and/or requirements. Skills website enhancements branding campaigns email marketing Education Bachelors (required) Qualifications Years of experience: 0 years Experience level:Experienced Shift: First Working hours: 8 AM - 4 PM Randstad is a world leader in matching great people with great companies. Our experienced agents will listen carefully to your employment needs and then work diligently to match your skills and qualifications to the right job and company. Whether you\'re looking for temporary, temporary-to-permanent or permanent opportunities, no one works harder for you than Randstad. EEO Employer: Race, Religion, Color, National Origin, Citizenship, Sex, Sexual Orientation, Gender Identity, Age, Disability, Ancestry, Veteran Status, Genetic Information, Service in the Uniformed Services or any other classification protected by law. San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance: Qualified applicants in San Francisco with criminal histories will be considered for employment in accordance with the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance. \n','Salary $30  -  $37   Per Hour','https://job-openings.monster.com/marketing-analyst-san-jose-ca-us-randstad/224640448'),(1,'Marketing Data Analyst','TEKsystems','San Jose, CA','Marketing Analyst','Description: The Digital Experience Analytics team is looking for a dynamic, data-driven Marketing Analyst with a strong blend of story-telling and technical expertise. B2B Digital Experience is an exciting, constantly evolving space that needs your skillset to drive marketing insights and generate long-term value for our client and its customers. In this role, you will be tasked with discovering and communicating customer-centric insights to your business partners by stitching together data from multiple sources. You are passionate about diving deep into the data and building reporting solutions to help you and your partners scale efficiently.  What you\'ll Do  - Quantify the impact of major marketing initiatives and communicate findings to key stakeholders (ongoing support mechanism to deliver data-driven insights) - Conduct end-to-end analyses to drive insights for marketing stakeholders around campaign performance and impact to sales pipeline  - Synthesize qualitative and quantitative data from multiple sources to support analytics goals  - Drive standardization and automation in marketing performance reporting across analysis and reporting deliverables  - Work with multiple technical, business teams, and Marketing Operations team to quickly diagnose, prioritize and scope marketing measurement implementation needs that will help deliver insights to optimize the business  - Build data pipelines and infrastructures to drive automation for yourself and the DX organization Skills: SQL, Excel, Marketo, B2B, PowerBI, Tableau, Marketing to Sales impact Top Skills Details: - Strong experience with SQL and Advanced Excel - Analytics experience supporting Marketing to impact Sales pipeline (understanding the marketing to sales impact, understanding enterprise sales journey) - Experience supporting B2B (B2B account-based marketing vs. B2C; how marketing functions in a B2B environment). Additional Skills & Qualifications: What You Need To Succeed 	Degree in Marketing, Statistics, Finance, Computer Science or other relevant fields 	Hands on job experience with analytics  	Ability to translate stakeholder asks into technical requirements to surface impactful end-state analyses and reports  	Experience with enterprise software applications such as Salesforce, Power BI, and Marketo  	Strong experience with SQL and Advanced Excel Required  	Outstanding problem solving and analytical skills including talent for conducting research, analyzing data, developing hypotheses, and synthesizing recommendations 	Ability to utilize combined industry benchmarking information with a strong analytical capability to identify market trends and test alternative approaches to strategy that yield superior performance  	High degree of intellectual curiosity and ability to absorb new concepts quickly  	Highly entrepreneurial and able to operate independently with minimal supervision 	Heavily results-oriented with a strong track record of meeting and/or exceeding internal project deadlines and deliverables  	Experience in subscription revenue environment is ideal \n \n About TEKsystems: \n We\'re partners in transformation. We help clients activate ideas and solutions to take advantage of a new world of opportunity. We are a team of 80,000 strong, working with over 6,000 clients, including 80% of the Fortune 500, across North America, Europe and Asia. As an industry leader in Full-Stack Technology Services, Talent Services, and real-world application, we work with progressive leaders to drive change. That\'s the power of true partnership. TEKsystems is an Allegis Group company.  \n The company is an equal opportunity employer and will consider all applications without regards to race, sex, age, color, religion, national origin, veteran status, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, genetic information or any characteristic protected by law.','Posted   2   days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/marketing-data-analyst-san-jose-ca-us-teksystems/84f92011-bfa8-46e0-885e-bba3e8424700'),(2,'VP of Product Management Enterprise','RingCentral','Belmont, CA','Marketing Analyst','Job Description:   The Vice President Product Management - Enterprise position is a high-impact role responsible for expanding Company \'s UCaaS capabilities for enterprise customers.  As PBX customers increasingly shift from on-premise to the cloud, Company needs to ensure that we are meeting the mission-critical telephony workflows of our enterprise customers.  Company is seeking a product leader with deep experience in telephony, VOIP, and PBX capabilities.  Additionally, you will be responsible for simplifying administration and deployment of our solutions at large companies.  As  VP of Product Management, Enterprise  you will be responsible for developing the roadmap and delivering the capabilities that meet the needs of our enterprise customers.  By delivering on this roadmap, you will help accelerate the transformation of 400 M on-premise PBX users to the cloud.  This is an opportunity to impact the lives of millions of UCaaS end-users in a positive way.  This role will work with cross-functional teams to launch new products and services.  You will work with engineering, security, operations, support, marketing, and sales to build and deliver products.  Responsibilities: Develop vision, product strategy, and priorities for Enterprise customers and core telephony/PBX capabilities Work closely with Sales to help unblock opportunities in the enterprise segment Collaborate with product marketing, analyst relations, and PR to communicate our enterprise and telephony capabilities Collaborate with engineering leadership to deliver value to customers Build relationships with customer IT executives Communicate our product vision and strategy to executive leadership and the company Track and measure the success of each product/feature launched Qualifications: 10+ years of product management experience delivering successful products at scale 5+ years of experience with UCaaS, Telephony, and PBX products Experience managing teams of 20+ product managers Experience working with enterprise customers and corporate IT departments Strong executive presence Excellent written and oral communication skills A strong bias for action and results Technical background or relevant experience Self-starter with ability to thrive in an entrepreneurial environment Bachelor \'s degree in Computer Science or Engineering Agile/Scrum experience Bonus: Experience working with geographically distributed team members Experience with messaging and video meeting products','Posted   17   days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/vp-of-product-management-enterprise-belmont-ca-us-ringcentral/4706cf97-8042-4973-a2a3-91a705b9fe30'),(3,'Marketing Automation Analyst','Zensar Technologies','San Jose, CA','Marketing Analyst','Marketing Automation Analyst San Jose, CA  Marketing automation experience knowledge i.e.  Eloqua Knowledge on Data Integrations (Snowflake, Mulesoft) Good Experience with SQL Queries - Data ( Tables, Records, Fields, Massive Volumes , Data Models, ER Diagrams, Data Governance ) i.e RDBMS/Data warehousing Good Experience with Agile Methodology ( Ability to creatively break down the work into chunks ( stories ) that realistically fit in Sprints ) Good Experience with Solution Proposals ( Propose Solutions that fit based on Biz and IT Requirements/Constraints & Get Agreements on a win-win proposal )','Job Type fulltime ,  contract','https://job-openings.monster.com/marketing-automation-analyst-san-jose-ca-us-zensar-technologies/224535127'),(4,'Data Scientist, Marketing','Airtable','San Francisco, CA','Marketing Analyst','Partner with Marketing leadership to help drive insights, identify opportunities, and understand behavior and long-term trends, working with other teams across the company in the process Take a leading role in producing new datasets that unlock growth and business opportunities Manage the design and analysis of marketing insights; develop and socialize a rigorous culture of data-driven decision making Play a foundational role in building a data culture at Airtable through reproducible work, improved processes, and better tooling, working with a full team of Data Scientists and Data Engineers Develop measurement and attribution methodologies, LTV models & comprehensive marketing analytics Collaborate with data engineering to build and evolve our data infrastructure to surface key metrics through automated dashboards and reports Partner with performance marketing to design and execute experiments, incrementality testing, media mix modeling, & spend ROI curves to enable robust performance marketing decision making Lead the development of propensity models and predictive KPIs to power targeting & optimization engines across marketing channels Who you are You have 5+ years previous experience as a marketing analyst, data scientist, or data analyst You have a familiarity with and passion for effec