unicating results to a broad audience Ability to prioritize and deliver within a fast-paced, dynamic environment ','Posted   6   days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/marketing-analyst-3-6-month-contract-santa-clara-ca-us-chegg/bb3ea749-ab98-415f-b1bd-36894f157647'),(14,'Marketing Analyst','Carlost Inc.','Burlingame, CA','Marketing Analyst','Produce innovative, simple solutions to design issues Design user flows and high-level behavior for new features Work with user interface designers to create beautiful mockups Collaborate with the engineering team to help determine the best implementation methods Understand our users and their educational needs Help diagnose and resolve user support issues Work with employees from other departments, including marketing, sales, and technical support, to gather requirements and coordinate projects Conduct competitive analysis and other research projects','Posted   27   days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/marketing-analyst-burlingame-ca-us-carlost-inc/b935a4ed-fcac-4a66-9a4b-09df4cf4b33e'),(15,'Customer Marketing Analyst','Intelliswift Software Inc','San Jose, CA','Marketing Analyst','The challenge \nThe Digital Experience Marketing Team team is looking for a Content Strategist to help plan and execute a content to support global campaigns. In this global role, you will partner closely with campaign marketing directors, campaign journey managers, creative directors, producers, and measurement teams. You will ensure campaign marketing assets are produced and available to the corporate and regional teams implementing programs. The role requires working cross functionally with internal stakeholders including demand marketing, partner marketing, product marketing, communications and other teams as required. \n \nWhat you\'ll do \n \n You will plan, develop, implement, and track the content required for integrated marketing campaigns that touch every part of the customer journey. \n Content strategy and orchestration: Develop a comprehensive strategy for content and assets required for the campaign by partnering with the journey manager to ensure content is aligned with the campaign strategy, customer journey, and relevant for the customer across channels. \n Program management: Share program strategy and solicit feedback from internal partners and channel owners  across advertising, PR, social, demand, field, and web  to plan engaging content experiences across customer journeys. You will be responsible for the overall program management of a complete content plan. \n Strategic briefs: Develop briefs that synthesize large amounts of information  from industry topics, to subject matter experts, to primary research  into audience-centric insights that can inspire our creative team to do their best work. \n Measurement: Work with marketing operations to define success metrics for campaign content. Set goals and measure influence on both pipeline creation and sales revenue. Work with both demand and field organizations to share insights for optimizing content for email, landing pages, videos, social and other channels. \n Budget management: Plan, track, and reconcile marketing budget for content creation in partnership with the creative and production team. You will manage costs within budget and work to minimize costs and maximize efficiency and effectiveness. \n \n Skills: \n \n What you need to succeed \n 3+ years content marketing experience in enterprise software or a technology related field \n Bachelor\'s degree, or equivalent work experience required \n Excellent written and verbal communication skills \n Self-starter with demonstrated ability to work in a dynamic marketing environment with global stakeholders \n Strong communications skills and experience in story-telling \n Understanding of customer segmentation, targeted personas and account intelligence processes to develop effective personalized communication to ensure relevant content reaches the right audience \n Understanding of global content needs and localization \n Precise attention to detail with creative acumen insightful analysis, ability to manage tactical details across multiple projects with flawless execution \n Strong interpersonal communication, teamwork & project management skills \n \n Knowledge of Client solutions desirable \nEducation: \nLanguages: \nEnglish Read Write Speak \n \nSkills:\n Required \n \n MARKETING \n PARTNER MARKETING \n PRODUCT MARKETING \n PROJECT MANAGEMENT \n ADVERTISING \n \n Additional \n \n BUDGET \n CONTENT CREATION \n EXCELLENT WRITTEN \n EXCELLENT WRITTEN AND VERBAL COMMUNICATION SKILLS \n METRICS \n OPERATIONS \n PR \n PRIMARY RESEARCH \n PROGRAM MANAGEMENT \n PUBLIC RELATIONS \n SALES REVENUE \n SEGMENTATION \n SELF-STARTER \n \nLanguages: English( Speak, Read, Write )','Posted 30+ days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/customer-marketing-analyst-san-jose-ca-us-intelliswift-software-inc/1395f04b-0a5f-4161-8991-79263e55abf2'),(16,'PASV: Junior Marketing Analyst at PASV - a Programming Academy from Silicon Valley (Remote)','Grintern','','Marketing Analyst','PASV  (Programming Academy in Silicon Valley) is an online programming school for Russian-speaking people in America. The school teaches people without IT experience the basics of programming and testing, prepares them for technical interviews, helps them build portfolios, and provides internship opportunities on commercial projects. Students of the school are also helped in finding employment - PASV guarantees to return the funds in double if you do not find a job within a year! The founder of the school, Viktor Bogutsky , is a programmer with a lot of experience - he worked in Russian and European IT companies for more than 15 years and to this day continues to work as a leading developer in Silicon Valley. Now the company collects and stores a lot of data that no one can analyze, so they are looking for a person to join their team for the position of a Junior Marketing Analyst who can analyze the indicators and understand what is going on. They need a person who can not only analyze the indicators and just build graphs or tables but also someone who can draw conclusions from that: for example, how much should the course cost, which advertising channels should be invested more, which courses bring more / less income, etc. What will you do? All the work processes will be built around analyzing the company\'s performance. Analyze the company\'s current advertising campaigns in Google Analytics & Google AdWords (how many people visited, from which advertising channel, etc.). Evaluate and optimize advertising campaigns that did not show the desired results. Help the company develop in new directions: you need to be able to conduct market analysis and understand which market the company can enter, analyze samples, competitors, etc. Take part in testing hypotheses and new directions of the company\'s development on the market. Requirements Good English skills: we want you to have at least an Upper-Intermediate level because there\'s a possibility that you\'ll communicate with PASV\'s competitors via e-mail. Otherwise, all the communication will be held in Russian. Experience in Google Analytics & Google AdWords. Independence and self-reliance: you can make decisions & be responsible for results without being constantly supervised Strong desire to learn from experienced people. Ability to focus on tasks: we expect you to take on tasks, do them well, and never leave them unfinished. Analytical mindset and ability to pay attention to every small detail. Ability to adjust to the EST time zone: you\'ll need to have overlapping hours for calls with Victor in the evenings (from 19:00 Moscow time), but other working hours can be flexible, it is more important to perform your tasks efficiently.  What we offer Part-time employment (4 working hours per day, 5/2). Please note that we support your desire to combine this job with studies, however, we will not