ey global themes, topics and events and awards that would inform our thought leadership campaign strategy.  Work cross-functionally with teams including marketing, analyst relations, customer references, etc. to build compelling, data-driven media pitches.  Contribute to our global storytelling efforts by using global and locally-relevant data points, customer stories and insights to generate positive press mentions in tier 1 media outlets and favorably shape the perception of NetApp as an industry leader among key stakeholders.  Proactively seek media opportunities and identify local and global active news cycles (or emerging ones) that we can leverage to share some relevant data points and position NetApp as a thought leader on current events/news.  Create, manage and nurture relationships with key journalists at tier 1 outlets and demonstrate an ability to bring an outside-in perspective to media relations to achieve consistent top tier results.  Support executive spokespeople throughout media engagements by providing them with media training, staffing interviews and managing required follow up.  Write high quality written materials including pitches, press releases, Q&A/FAQ, contributed articles and keynote presentations.  Partner with the NetApp internal Social Media team and local PR agency to localize corporate social media messages, amplify top PR results and engage in relevant conversations across local channels.  Partner with the Events Marketing team to support our event presence.   Support monthly and quarterly reporting of KPIs using Cision/Trendkite. Job Requirements Skills & Experience:  8+ years of corporate communications or public relations engaging directly with media, preferably in the technology industry.  Excellent written and oral communication skills.   Established relationships with tier 1 business, news and tech media outlets in the U.S.  Track of record of building, pitching and managing stories with top tier outlets.  Demonstrates a strategic mindset with solid business acumen.  Highly organized and detail-oriented.  Ability to maintain quality work under tight deadlines with the ability to prioritize and manage multiple projects simultaneously.  Adaptability.   Comfortable with ambiguity.  Experience coordinating high-touch media events including supporting spokespeople, developing content and managing detailed planning and logistics.  Experience developing sticky social media content for Twitter, LinkedIn, Facebook and more.   Current knowledge of digital communications techniques, media monitoring best practices, stakeholder briefing and coaching.  Bachelors degree or higher required with emphasis in journalism, public relations, marketing, or communications. Education BS/BA degree or equivalent related experience. 8+ years -- plus add additional experience requirements needed if you were to fill an open requisition, i.e., knowledge, skills, and abilities. Nearest Major Market:  San Jose Nearest Secondary Market:  Palo Alto Job Segment: Strategist, Social Media, Corporate Communications, Cloud, PR, Strategy, Marketing, Technology','Posted 30+ days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/global-thought-leadership-program-strategist-sunnyvale-ca-us-netapp/b4ce5799-c486-4807-9426-4e9b4d251a9f'),(27,'Sr. Staff Data Analyst (Marketing Multi Product)','Freedom Financial Network','San Mateo, CA','Marketing Analyst','WHO WE ARE: Voted one of the Top 100 Fastest Growing Companies in the Bay Area for 2020, Freedom Financial Network is a family of companies that takes a people-first approach to financial services, using technology to empower consumers to overcome debt and create a brighter financial future. The company was founded in 2002 by Brad Stroh and Andrew Housser on the belief that by staying committed to helping people, you can ensure better financial outcomes for both the customer and the business. This Heart + $ philosophy still guides the vision of our growing company, which has helped millions o