es and organizations the power to truly engage their customers. We\'re the ones behind the gorgeously designed content that streams across your laptop, TV, phone, and tablet every day?and we\'re the ones who harness the massive power of big data to help companies move from data to insight and insight to action by delivering content that people crave most. The challenge The Digital Experience Marketing Team team is looking for a Content Strategist to help plan and execute a content to support global campaigns. In this global role, you will partner closely with campaign marketing directors, campaign journey managers, creative directors, producers, and measurement teams. You will ensure campaign marketing assets are produced and available to the corporate and regional teams implementing programs. The role requires working cross functionally with internal stakeholders including demand marketing, partner marketing, product marketing, communications and other teams as required. What you\'ll do You will plan, develop, implement, and track the content required for integrated marketing campaigns that touch every part of the customer journey. Content strategy and orchestration: Develop a comprehensive strategy for content and assets required for the campaign by partnering with the journey manager to ensure content is aligned with the campaign strategy, customer journey, and relevant for the customer across channels. Program management: Share program strategy and solicit feedback from internal partners and channel owners ? across advertising, PR, social, demand, field, and web ? to plan engaging content experiences across customer journeys. You will be responsible for the overall program management of a complete content plan. Strategic briefs: Develop briefs that synthesize large amounts of information ? from industry topics, to subject matter experts, to primary research ? into audience-centric insights that can inspire our creative team to do their best work. Measurement: Work with marketing operations to define success metrics for campaign content. Set goals and measure influence on both pipeline creation and sales revenue. Work with both demand and field organizations to share insights for optimizing content for email, landing pages, videos, social and other channels. Budget management: Plan, track, and reconcile marketing budget for content creation in partnership with the creative and production team. You will manage costs within budget and work to minimize costs and maximize efficiency and effectiveness. What you need to succeed 3+ years content marketing experience in enterprise software or a technology related field Bachelor\'s degree, or equivalent work experience required Excellent written and verbal communication skills Self-starter with demonstrated ability to work in a dynamic marketing environment with global stakeholders Strong communications skills and experience in story-telling Understanding of customer segmentation, targeted personas and account intelligence processes to develop effective personalized communication to ensure relevant content reaches the right audience Understanding of global content needs and localization Precise attention to detail with creative acumen? insightful analysis, ability to manage tactical details across multiple projects with flawless execution Strong interpersonal communication, teamwork & project management skills Knowledge of Adobe solutions desirable','Posted 30+ days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/customer-marketing-analyst-2-san-jose-ca-us-talentburst-inc/2e8d9e5c-993a-4c08-9ebe-502dfc315dc9'),(50,'Growth Marketing Analyst','FormSwift','San Francisco or Remote, CA','Marketing Analyst','Search Engine Marketing (SEM) is the discipline of creating, monitoring, and managing advertising campaigns on search engines. The majority of FormSwifts customers come from text ads on Google and Microsoft, and at the same time, Search advertising is a major company expense. For these and other reasons, the Growth Marketing Analyst will fill a role that is central to our success, and will work closely with colleagues from other specialties, particularly developers, designers, product managers, and business managers. The advertising industry has evolved greatly in the past few decades. While traditional types of advertising  from radio jingles to Superbowl commercials to celebrity sponsorships to billboardsremain important, companies like Google and Microsoft have led a quiet revolution in the advertising space. As an SEM analyst, you will work with Google and Microsofts ad platforms. Google ads takes in roughly $50B per year from advertisers like us, and has become the most valuable platform on Earth because it offers three features that are largely absent from traditional media: 1.  Measurement.  In SEM, we track every dollar spent on advertisements and every penny earned as a result. For all of FormSwifts customers, we know what advertisement the customer clicked on, how much was spent to serve the ad, what the exact text of the advertisement read, how the customer moved through our website, what the customer purchased , where and when every step of the process occurred, and much more. This allows us to determine the profitability of our advertising activities with high granularity. 2.  Control.  We can serve highly-customized advertisements to potential customers based on what the customer is searching for, their past search history, prior activity on our website, the customers location, time of day, day of week, etc. We can also control how aggressively we market to users based on these same variables, which lets us dedicate our spending towards messaging users who are the most likely to be interested in FormSwifts services and are most likely to become satisfied long-term customers. 3.  Algorithmic Bidding.  Advertising space on search engines is allocated using an auction model. When you search on Google or any other search engine, an auction occurs in the milliseconds that elapse between when you strike the Enter key and when the results appear. Different advertisers bid against each other to serve ads to specific users, and the results page you seewhich may be absolutely unique to youis the outcome of that auction. These auctions occur so quickly that bidding is necessarily algorithmic. Rather than gathering in a hotel ballroom and frantically waving numbered cards in the air in front of a fast-talking auctioneer, we design bidding strategies that can be executed by computers, and search engines provide a set of tools to advertisers like FormSwift to craft such algorithms.','Posted   9   days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/growth-marketing-analyst-san-francisco-or-remote-ca-us-formswift/c5795b6e-d9a3-4961-9e54-5ddc92e692dd'),(51,'Senior Manager Corporate Public Relations & U.S. Lead','NetApp','Sunnyvale, CA','Marketing Analyst','Title:Senior Manager Corporate Public Relations & U.S. Lead Location: Sunnyvale, CA, US, 94089 Requisition ID:64966 Job Summary Senior Manager, Corporate Public Relations and U.S. Lead Job Summary  NetApp, a global cloud-led, data-centric software company, is seeking a self-motivated, seasoned and creative corporate communications professional to join our team as the Senior Manager of Corporate Public Relations and U.S. Lead. This role will be responsible for leading the U.S. Public Relations team and developing and executing strategic corporate public relations plans that drive awareness to market impact in the U.S. This role will contribute to our global storytelling efforts by generating positive press mentions in tier-1 media outlets and favorably shape the external perception of NetApp. The ideal candidate for this role has a track record of driving strategic corporate public relations programs and generating press mentions in tier 1 outlets. Data-driven and KPIs-oriented, she/he/they are a strategic thinker who can thrive in a global fast-paced environment. Exceptiona