m members to evangelize the email marketing program, increase customer engagement, optimize email communications and support sales activities. The Email Marketing Analyst will be responsible for conducting analysis, improving efficiency, and providing insight to management about the performance of the email marketing program, as well as ensuring best practices. This role is perfect for a multi-skilled, self-sufficient and motivated individual who has expertise in executing email marketing, Salesforce, and marketing campaigns that drive measurable business results. We are a small, scrappy team, so there will be opportunity to help across marketing, from event planning to web page launches to data appending. Primary Responsibilities: * Assist in executing and evangelizing email marketing program strategies including the development of marketing and transactional emails, maintaining the email marketing calendar, determining testing strategies, communicating business requirements, measuring results, and managing overall process to drive and achieve new partner growth * Manage Pardot Admin tasks, including user management, roles, permissions, automations, data restructuring and cleanup, and other related tasks. * Support in Pardot migration process with opportunity to take over entire project * Analyze metrics and build into reports/dashboards for team and stakeholders. Determine and suggest appropriate courses of action based on findings. * Manage data and audience segmentation * Develop and enforce workflows, manage requests, timelines and communication with stakeholders * Build, edit, test and send html emails * Manage the quarterly newsletter from start to finish: reaching out to stakeholders to gather content, organizing content, building and testing the email, managing edits and approvals, creating dynamic content, managing lists, and reporting. * Configure fields in Pardot as well as the linked Salesforce environment as needed for data collection. * Work with our 