itical questions about data and always ready to solve any challenges Excellent communication, relationship skills, and a strong team player. #LI-FRESH','Posted 30+ days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/marketing-data-analyst-san-francisco-ca-us-talentburst-inc/d810902a-34c9-496e-843a-10c369fc0106'),(64,'Marketing Data Analyst','ICONMA, LLC','San Francisco, CA','Marketing Analyst','Marketing Data Analyst  Location: San Francisco, CA Duration: 12 months Description:   Be the key point of liaison regarding media spend data with our media agency partners. You will be the primary steward of organizing our spend and forward looking data into highly polished and easily interpreted presentations. You\'ll also be working with our Global Agencies to ensure reporting data is delivered on time, at scale, and compliance with all of client policies. Media Lab Operations Coordination: Understand how to gather, analyze and organize data to meet business objectives and convey results and insights to be variety of stakeholders using BI and/or visualization software Project Manage: Weekly campaign, publisher + top partner reporting Monthly global media calendar Real time reporting on scoped vs actual campaign spend tracking Recognize opportunities to deliver more efficiently by automating reporting queries, setting up recurring reports, creating dashboards for key use cases and stakeholders, etc. Maintain detailed documentation of all requests, data parameters & reports in an accurate and accessible manner Serve as a resource for new marketers who are learning to use reporting and governance tools, understand their specific use case and help them either pull reporting, input a new media request, or resolve a compliance violation. Media Agency Coordination:   Manage media PO and Media Authorization Form approval process to ensure compliance with media plan targets   Manage Global Media Agency campaign reporting deliverables and ensure reporting lags do not impact global data pull