nable our merchants to transact with payment processors worldwide. The successful candidate will work closely with business product managers, engineers, architects, user experience, and global cross-functional counterparts. If you have strong analytical skills, a curious mindset, and a strong desire to create a career in technical product management, come talk to us. You will get a chance to work with some of the brightest payment professionals and take your career to new heights. You will be part of the Technical Product Management organization which will enable Visa and its subsidiaries such as Cybersource, Authorize.Net, Verify, as well its strategic partners to rapidly build, iterate and refine payment experiences across all channels such as web and mobile. We have a start-up mentality, take smart risks, solve important problems, and adapt and iterate quickly. We are looking for someone who is passionate about the payments space to join a team that is made stronger through innovation and collaboration. Essential Functions: Be hands-on with describing business rules as technical artifacts for analysts, business product managers, and any functional team that depends on this information Define business rules in a proprietary tool using a proprietary language, perform unit tests, resolve bugs and be responsible for the delivery of the project to production Be comfortable looking at system logs when needed and identifying bugs when they might appear during course of analysis Work with technical product managers and business product managers to understand the requirements and receive technical specifications Work with architects and engineers to come up solutions addressing business needs Analyze technical specifications and create user stories for engineering and test engineering teams Be the product owner for the scrum teams driving project execution Maintain the metrics for the product/capabilities Highly execution focused by working in conjunction with various cou