ties for growth or to deliver a superior customer experience? How good are we at what we do and where can we improve? If you are BI-minded and lean product enthusiast youll fit right in at Chargebee. This is a great opportunity for a talented analyst to level up their skills on a path to general management or product leadership roles. Your mission will be to quickly bring accurate evidence to the table when important decisions need to be made at all levels of the organization, especially within Product Management. What you would actually be doing: Contribute in aggregating data from different systems in our organization within our Tableau instance Organize and cleanse data, identifying data integrity issues and resolutions to the same Utilize data to analyze product development investment and return attributed to customer segments, user personas, and product lines. Prepare weekly, monthly and quarterly internal reports and find visual ways to articulate critical insights Partner with Product managers to help them understand where users find value Onboard members of the organization to using existing reports or generating custom views based upon report templates and data snapshots you\'d expose to them Support the product leadership organization with data and insights for the Board of Directors Identify trends that influence performance; both in terms of the customer impact and internal company performance Collaborate with other departments in the organization (BI, Engineering, Customer Success, Solutions, Sales, Marketing, HR, Finance) to improve data availability, integrity and collection Advise on tools selection and best practices in processes for data collection and management to continuously improve our operations by automating tracking, gathering, correlating, analyzing and reporting. Evangelise a data-centric culture and drive alignment between departments on relevant topics Looking ahead, create models to illustrate the long-term effects of strategic decisions Qualifications 3+ year experience as a product BI analyst or similar roles (can be in BI consulting, sales/marketing BI, etc) Excellent English communication skills Experience with BI visualization in Tableau Handy with xls, SQL, Python, R Experience configuring and querying tools like: Salesforce, Jira, GIT Experience with web analytics and event tracking tools such as Google Analytics and Pendo etc Expert on data visualization and a statistics-lover Bonus points! Its an absolute plus if you have a strong understanding of the Product Management processes and have worked in product before An extra plus if you have an understanding of the different functions involved in governing, marketing, and selling software products (processes and practices) Financial literacy and/or user behavior analyses are also pluses! If this sounds interesting but youre not sure you\'ll tick all the boxes, apply anyway! Theres tons of room to grow at Chargebee!','Posted   9   days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/product-analyst-remote-any-location-california-us-chargebee/4f1d2abc-810c-49ef-9cdb-2d97288a034e'),(19,'Product Analyst','Redolent, Inc','San Bruno, CA','Product Analyst','\nOne of our direct client is urgently looking for  Product Analyst @ San Bruno, CA \n \n TITLE:  Product Analyst \n LOCATION: San Bruno, CA \n DURATION: 6 Months  \nRate: DOE \nProduct Analyst [Level 1 Support] \n \n Position Summary \nClient is looking for a strong individual with leadership skills who excels in market place product analysis. The person also would need to have strong verbal and written communication to address the product/technical issues. \n \n Responsibilities and activities include: \nUnderstand business flows, tools, trouble shoot and support seller issues using tools. \nOngoing management of seller issues, queries and operational issues. \nCoordination of issue resolution across business, production support, business support analyst and functional teams in the context of specific