ve. Daily, Gracenote processes 35 billion rows of data and is quickly becoming a world-leader in return path big data. Over the past 3 years, the company has grown to more than 2000 employees in 17 countries, including over 600 of the worlds top engineers with a passion for music, video, sports, and entertainment technology. Founded in 1998, Gracenote is one of Americas most iconic and respected media companies.  Our team seeks someone passionate about data to join us as a Product Analyst. Product Analysts know our data inside and out and leverage this knowledge and tools to improve product performance, quality and end consumer experience. The ideal candidate is proactive to identify product issues, analytical to identify patterns, data driven to drive decisions and will work closely with Product Managers, Content, and Engineering.   RESPONSIBILITIES    Develop deeper product understanding and be proactive to identify product quality and performance issues. Collect and analyze data to draw insight and identify solutions for our radio and music product offerings   Conduct business performance analysis across products and features   Drive product performance and quality metrics, analyzing Gracenotes datasets against the client/customer experience   Continuous learning from on-going QC and results to improve upon product KPIs   Develop tools to present dashboards and findings around usage, performance, and stability to varying audiences/stakeholders to support product decisions and roadmap   Manage ad hoc reports and quantitative analysis to iron out bugs and issues with engineering   Work closely with cross-functional stakeholders to gather data requirements and oversee process implementation   QUALIFICATIONS    3+ years post-collegiate work experience in a quantitative/data analytics field or equivalent educational experience focused on data analysis   Ability to synthesize complex datasets into simple and compelling information   Highly motivated, proactive and able