oducts or with internationally distributed teams. As an equal opportunity employer, ICONMA prides itself on creating an employment environment that supports and encourages the abilities of all persons regardless of race, color, gender, age, sexual orientation, citizenship, or disability ','Posted 30+ days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/product-operations-analyst-iii-mountain-view-ca-us-iconma-llc/35d8dc0b-4489-430f-a561-f239374522fb'),(64,'Business Analyst with Product Master Specialist@ Santa Clara, CA','Diverse Lynx','Santa Clara, CA','Product Analyst','\n \n \n Role  \n Business Analyst with Product Master Specialist \n \n \n LocationSanta Clara,CA \n \n \n \n Roles & Responsibilities  \n \n Good understanding of SDLC and Agile methodologies \n Engage with business stakeholders to understand business requirements & demonstrate ability to develop and prepare business analysis, plans & business requirement definitions \n Support the functional design and implementation of projects and create solutions to meet business objectives and resolve system / process issues \n Responsible for business process understanding of data consumption.  \n Extensive validation skills of the gathered data for veracity, consistency, and completeness \n Develop a strategic vision and roadmap that is forward looking and serves as interface to the overall business strategy \n Identify smarter ways to identify anomaly within the customer master \n Design and implement AI-Client for automated pattern identification and data remediation \n Analyse data and work directly with Business data owners to define and draft business rules  \n Troubleshoot data problems and drive closed-loop corrective action process \n \n Requirements  \n \n 9+ years of experience in Data Management Practices and methodologies  \n Experience with Product Master or knowledge of product master data attributes, product hierarchy, Attribute based Product Models is a must. \n Responsible for business process under