inimum qualifications Professional experience with classical statistics (regression, time series, clustering) and/or machine learning (supervised and unsupervised) Professional experience with large databases and SQL Professional experience visualizing data in Tableau, Google Sheets/Excel, R, Python Proficiency with building beautiful, visually consistent presentations (Google Slides, Powerpoint, Keynote) Bachelors degree in data quantitative field (Statistics, Computer Science, Economics, etc.) Skills Must be a flexible and creative individual capable of managing multiple priorities and projects in a diverse environment Must be able to achieve results in a culture that favors collaborative decision making Excellent leadership and organizational management skills Excellent use of communication and productivity tools Strong analytical and problem solving skills Superb verbal and written communications skills Experience working with staff and stakeholders that are geographically dispersed Desired Preferred qualifications: Outstanding analytical skills and strong understanding of statistical modeling techniques Ability to lead and handle multiple time-sensitive projects Superb communication skills Creative, results driven, able to zoom from strategy to execution, business minded, and collaborative Graduate degree in data quantitative field (Statistics, Computer Science, Economics, etc.) As an equal opportunity employer, ICONMA prides itself on creating an employment environment that supports and encourages the abilities of all persons regardless of race, color, gender, age, sexual orientation, citizenship, or disability. ','Posted 30+ days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/data-scientist-iii-mountain-view-ca-us-iconma-llc/2ea30cbb-e57d-41ab-8883-34dcf23d1dce'),(68,'Product Systems Analyst','ICONMA, LLC','San Francisco, CA','Product Analyst','Product Systems Analyst Location: San Francisco, CA Duration: 11-12 months  Description: The client BIz Tech Legal, Compliance, and Security (LCS) team is seeking an experienced Product Systems Analyst with a background in delivery for Governance, Risk, and Compliance stakeholders within a global organization. You will be a key individual contributor on the LCS team. The successful candidate possesses strong analytical, written, oral and consulting skills, able to articulate and document functional requirements, influence the solution design for business users and the development team. This role is within the Information Technology organization primarily supporting our GRC and Compliance stakeholders, a global, multi-arm organization within client website. Our ideal candidate must possess the business and technical skills/experience prescribed, enjoy working in a highly dynamic, fast-paced and high-growth environment, as well as be experienced at managing complex projects and stakeholder groups in support of the LCS portfolio.  Responsibilities: Engage with the business users at different levels to understand Compliance business needs, analyze, document, evaluate and prioritize the requirements and make recommendations on the solution and implementation. Drive, develop and maintain numerous project deliverables that support the program, including functional/non-functional specifications, data mapping/transformation, solution design, process diagram, acceptance criteria, UAT scripts and other project artifacts. Work effectively with the solution and technical teams to help them understand the specifications/requirements for technical development, testing and implementation. Identify test scenarios, develop test scripts, and execute testing in support of system and User Acceptance Testing (UAT). Partner with various business partners and solution teams to evaluate GRC tool and feature usage and recommend best approaches Ensure solutions promote simplicity, efficiency, and conform to enterprise and architecture standards and guidelines. Provide functional leadership during technology enhancements/upgrades/ implementations and work successfully as a liaison with various internal business/ technical partners. Partner with the support organization to provide training, support and technical assistance to operations team and end users. Participate in Agile scrum team, write/enhance/research user stories and be responsible as business lead and central subject matter expert. Help streamline work process to improve efficiency and consistency.  Required Skills/Experience: Bachelors Degree with 3-5 years of hands-on experience as a business system analyst type role implementing enterprise software, preferably in the areas of GRC, Compliance, and Risk Management Strong background in driving business requirement workshops, assessments, and the resulting solutions Experience in working with both the business and technical teams, coordinating/leading solution design, development/configuration, and deployment across multi-dimensional teams. Strong background in business process analysis, data modeling and ability to proactively identify and manage mapping of requirements to business processes and the underlying data. Ability to quickly connect business requirements to the functional capabilities of an application and assess the applicability of different product technologies to business problems; ability to learn new applications and technologies. Proven ability to coordinate a diverse set of business users to develop cohesive and streamlined requirements, documentation and user acceptance criteria. Excellent spoken and written communication as well as receptive listening skills, with ability to present complex ideas in a clear, concise fashion to technical and non-technical audiences. Excellent team player able to work with virtual and global cross functional teams with the flexibility to work in different time zones.  Desired Skills/Experience: Experience with leading GRC technologies and platforms, such as MetricStream, RSA Archer, etc. Possess Compliance functional domain knowledge with experience in GRC, Internal/External Audit processes, Risk Management, and Issue Management. In addition to the above, can operate across muliple stakeholder groups, analyze and communicate conflicting/synergizing priorities with different Product Management teams, and work with a global delivery team. Experience implementing Governance, Risk, and Compliance tools is a plus.  As an equal opportunity employer, ICONMA prides itself on creating an employment environment that supports and encourages the abilities of all persons regardless of race, color, gender, age, sexual orientation, citizenship, or disability.','Posted 30+ days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/product-systems-analyst-san-francisco-ca-us-iconma-llc/a576a585-9aee-4216-ac15-a77bdd2a01bb');
