INSERT INTO `bay_area_sa` VALUES (0,'Finance and Strategy Analyst - Hardware FP&A','Square','San Francisco, CA','Strategy Analyst','Square builds common business tools in unconventional ways so more people can start, run, and grow their businesses. When Square started, it was difficult and expensive (or just plain impossible) for some businesses to take credit cards. Square made credit card payments possible for all by turning a mobile phone into a credit card reader. Since then Square has been building an entire business toolkit of both hardware and software products including Square Capital, Square Terminal, Square Payroll, and more. Were working to find new and better ways to help businesses succeed on their own termsand were looking for people like you to help shape tomorrow at Square. Job Description We are looking for an Analyst to support the Hardware business with a mandate that focuses on finance processes, systems, and data scale with Squares growth. You will partner directly with other finance team members and Hardware business partners on important elements of operational execution such as procurement, team and company headcount management, and management reporting. You will help guide process efficiencies within the finance team. We are open to having this position be full-time remote but you will need to be in the Pacific or Mountain time zones. You Will: Manage and centralize important operational aspects of the finance team, including areas related to: Management reporting: you will perform analysis and provide insight for regular variance to budget reporting and support key budget and investment decisions with emphasis on our Hardware logistics (warehousing, fulfillment), operational expenses, and capital expenditures Headcount management: Squares largest financial investment is in its people; you will coordinate with business, recruiting and HR partners to manage detailed headcount planning efforts. Procurement: you will partner closely with business areas to manage bottoms-up budget builds and tracking to budget. Demonstrate a mindset of continuous improvement to improve efficiency within F&S and improve business partnering across Square. Collaborate to guide important initiatives such as process improvement and standardization, system enhancements, and data governance. Help create finance process documentation, training guides, and resources. You will become an expert for finance process and policy questions and support business partners and new manager training. Build trust with finance team members and business leaders at Square Qualifications You Have: 1+ years of relevant experience in finance operations, FP&A, audit, accounting, and/or procurement but not required Bachelors Degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting, or other relevant field Prior experience with financial planning systems and financial planning processes within larger finance organizations; experience in the technology industry and/or supply chain management is a plus but not required. Additional Information At Square, we value diversity and always treat all employees and job applicants based on merit, qualifications, competence, and talent. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. We will consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the requirements of the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance. Applicants in need of special assistance or accommodation during the interview process or in accessing our website may contact us by sending an email to assistance(at)squareup.com. We will treat your request as confidentially as possible. In your email, please include your name and preferred method of contact, and we will respond as soon as possible. Perks At Square, we want you to be well and thrive. Our global benefits package includes: Healthcare coverage Retirement Plans Employee Stock Purchase Program Wellness perks Paid parental leave Paid time off Learning and Development resources','Posted   9   days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/finance-strategy-analyst-hardware-fp-a-san-francisco-ca-us-square/d8666413-0aa5-4d9d-8054-20500d8901a9'),(1,'Medical Affairs Vendor Strategy Analyst  US Drug Safety','Ascent Services Group','South San Francisco, CA','Strategy Analyst','Vendor Strategy Analyst US Drug Safety South San Francisco, CA (need to be local but will start remote) Department:  Commercial |Medical Affairs | US Drug Safety | US Drug Safety Job Category:  Medical Affairs Type : Initial 12-monthcontract (w2) Option to extend up to 36-months Pay Range:  $40 - $52.00/hr Job Description:   Understands the vendor management framework set by the Head of PV Operations and Vendor Strategy Manager and translates the requirements into reporting deliverables (e.g., QA/QC metrics, action items, etc.)   Works with the Vendor Lead on the oversight of GVP Vendors   Facilitates and participates in vendor and PV oversight activities such as vendor meetings   Communicates closely with local cross functional teams within US Drug Safety (USDS) to ensure the appropriate level of support is achieved to ensure oversight.   Determines priorities and resource load balancing to manage backlogs, action items, and business as usual.   Leads, coordinates, and collates QC error rates, QC metrics, trends, and gaps for the Vendor Strategy Manager and Vendor Strategy Lead.   Leads or assists in the tracking and investigation of case processing related metrics including compliance related issues set by the vendor management strategy.   Understands the PV environment and works with Vendor Strategy Lead and Vendor Strategy Manager to identify vendor compliance risks. Skills:   Exemplifies strong, dynamic leadership and demonstrates decisiveness and appropriate decision-making abilities as demonstrated by systematic gathering of information, appropriately assessing the complexity of issues, and prioritization of tasks in a timely manner within the scope of responsibility and escalates identified issues to management in a timely fashion.   Works effectively, independently, and collaboratively as a team member with global stakeholders and external business partners   Strong organizational skills, detail oriented and adapts in a fast paced, changing environment   Demonstrates ownership, initiative, accountability, strong organizational skills, and is solution oriented   Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal   Ability to actively exchange knowledge and ideas   Able to identify potential business gaps and leads in the development and implementation of process solutions   Able to handle the pressure associated with and adapts to a fast-paced, changing environment   Inspires others to do their best work by offering encouragement and support   Maintains personal and corporate integrity Education:   Life sciences degree - BSc is the  minimum   5+ years in pharmacovigilance or similar compliance-related role required   Advanced analytic and computer skills (e.g., Microsoft Excel, other data visualization tools)   Medical terminology experience   Writing experience inscience/medical writing   Able to travel as per business needs (eventually) required   Able to be agile and adapt to shifting priorities and needs   Able to be flexible to accommodate differences in vendor time zones','Job Type fulltime ,  employee','https://job-openings.monster.com/medical-affairs-vendor-strategy-analyst-us-drug-safety-south-san-francisco-ca-us-ascent-services-group/225115056'),(2,'Corporate Strategy Analyst - (B4)','Applied Materials','Santa Clara, CA','Strategy Analyst','Job Description Join a fun corporate strategy team and help shape Applied Materials future. You will work collaboratively across business units, sales, and operations teams to solve complex business problems through actionable insights. Initially an individual contributor, you will overtime become a subject matter expert in the semiconductor capital equipment industry and lead functional projects and teams.  Minimum qualifications:    Bachelors degree with strong financial modeling experience    2-4 year experience in Equity Research or Management Consulting    Strong verbal and written communication skills to communicate cross-functionally with all levels of management Preferred Qualifications:    MBA and / or CFA Level 2 passed    Expert level Excel modeling and data analytics skills    Semiconductor and Semiconductor Capital Equipment industry knowledge Responsibilities:    Create and maintain detailed financial models for semiconductor and semiconductor capital equipment companies, including product level and device level financial forecasts    Distill and communicate insights from data driven analyses, including using charts and tables to effectively illustrate key takeaways    Build strong relationships across the company and industry to stay abreast of the competitive landscape of the semiconductor and semiconductor capital equipment industry    Assist in the identification of secular trends in the broader technology sector and development of strategies to capture key inflections  #LI Qualifications Education: Bachelor\'s Degree Skills Certifications: Languages: Years of Experience: 4 - 7 Years Work Experience: Additional Information Travel: Yes, 25% of the Time Relocation Eligible: No Applied Materials is committed to diversity in its workforce including Equal Employment Opportunity for Minorities, Females, Protected Veterans and Individuals with Disabilities. \",\"value\":\" Job Description Join a fun corporate strategy team and help shape Applied Materials future. You will work collaboratively across business units, sales, and operations teams to solve complex business problems through actionable insights. Initially an individual contributor, you will overtime become a subject matter expert in the semiconductor capital equipment industry and lead functional projects and teams.  Minimum qualifications:    Bachelors degree with strong financial modeling experience    2-4 year experience in Equity Research or Management Consulting    Strong verbal and written communication skills to communicate cross-functionally with all levels of management Preferred Qualifications:    MBA and / or CFA Level 2 passed    Expert level Excel modeling and data analytics skills    Semiconductor and Semiconductor Capital Equipment industry knowledge Responsibilities:    Create and maintain detailed financial models for semiconductor and semiconductor capital equipment companies, including product level and device level financial forecasts    Distill and communicate insights from data driven analyses, including using charts and tables to effectively illustrate key takeaways    Build strong relationships across the company and industry to stay abreast of the competitive landscape of the semiconductor and semiconductor capital equipment industry    Assist in the identification of secular trends in the broader technology sector and development of strategies to capture key inflections  #LI Qualifications Education: Bachelor\'s Degree Skills Certifications: Languages: Years of Experience: 4 - 7 Years Work Experience: Additional Information Travel: Yes, 25% of the Time Relocation Eligible: No Applied Materials is committed to diversity in its workforce including Equal Employment Opportunity for Minorities, Females, Protected Veterans and Individuals with Disabilities.','Posted   1   Day ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/corporate-strategy-analyst-b4-santa-clara-ca-us-applied-materials/12c4cd83-c41a-44e1-a34f-8acee4196212'),(3,'Go-to-Market & Strategy Analyst','Zoox','Foster City, CA','Strategy Analyst','In this role, you will be responsible for driving key strategic decisions in what could become a $10T global market for personal mobility. You will structure solutions to complex problems, perform deep data-driven analytics, generate insights, & then build cross-functional consensus among the senior management team to enable focused execution. You will be joining a diverse group of industry leaders & makers, where team success is as important as individual contributions. If you are excited about solving difficult problems and the opportunity to help define what an autonomous vehicle can be, we want to hear from you!','Posted 30+ days ago','https://job-openings.monster.com/go-to-market-strategy-analyst-foster-city-ca-us-zoox/c0acdec4-f38a-4a22-855b-613164db8349'),(4,'New Strategy Analyst','Fisher Careers','San Mateo, CA','Strategy Analyst','Overview  Are you motivated by helping companies grow and building new alternative investment strategies and capabilities? Do you have a passion for research and have experience conducting due diligence on investment managers? If so, the New Strategy Analyst within our Institutional group may be the right fit for you!   The Opportunity:  The Fisher Investments Institutional Group serves a global client base of diverse investors including public and multi-employer pension funds, foundations and endowments, insurance companies, healthcare organizations and more.  As a New Strategy Analyst, you will identify new opportunities for expansion. Reporting to a Vice President, you will monitor global institutional investor demand and introduce new approaches and capabilities based on your research and analysis. You will collaborate with Sales, Relationship Managers, Portfolio Management and more to manage projects from start to finish.   The Day-to-Day: Oversee the creation and lifecycle of new Institutional strategies including ideation, efficacy analysis, marketing, training, advocacy, and sales support Create and develop training tools and marketing materials for new strategies Guide Institutional team members in the creation of materials, analysis and responses to RFPs  Evaluate competitors by looking at all data and performance, culture, stability and more Communicate in detail on a number of topics with senior management and relationship managers  Manage all phases of multiple projects from vision through deployment  Identify potential process improvements, recommend and implement solutions to improve the efficiency of the department Join prospect, client and consultant meetings Your Qualifications: 5+ years of experience evaluating alternative investment managers (e.g. private equity, private debt, real assets/real estate, infrastructure, hedge funds, multi-assets, etc.) Experienced in research and competitive analysis  Interpersonal skills and professionalism Experience managing several projects and using insights to guide decisions Why Fisher Investments:  At Fisher Investments, we work for a bigger purpose: bettering the investment universe. From unmatched service to unique perspectives on investing, its the people that make the Fisher purpose possible. And we invest in them by offering exceptional benefits like: 100% coverage of premiums for health, vision and dental insurance A 50% 401(k) match, up to the IRS maximum 20 days of PTO*, plus 9 paid holidays 8 weeks paid Primary Caregiver Parental Leave Back-up Child Care Program available, offering up to 10 days annually A cumulative learning and development framework customized for every employee An award-winning work environment - we\'re Great Place to Work Certified, and Top Workplace winners from The Oregonian We take great pride in our inclusive culture. We value the different perspectives and unique skills you bring to the team  it makes us all better.Success at Fisher Investments is motivated by results, a collaborative mindset and a commitment to accomplishing great things  so if you are ready to do that, we are ready for you! Apply today to be a part of a team environment where you make a difference in the lives of people by bettering the investment universe.  *California employees accrue up to 17 days of PTO and 3 days